cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper deals with a visual tracking algorithm that utilizes deep reinforcement learning methods for template selection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of policy gradient methods for learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The algorithm also involves decision making, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of confidence maps, which are commonly used in robotics and control systems, indicating the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.RO (Robotics) as well. Finally, the use of deep reinforcement learning methods suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
